eset.title: day0
eset.source_name_ch1: Human induced pluripotent stem cell line  (201B7 MHC-GFP)
eset.characteristics_ch1: cell type: Undifferentiated human induced pluripotent stem cells
eset.treatment_protocol_ch1: After cardiac differentiation, we collected GFP positive cardiomyocytes by FACS sorting on day9, 21, and 30. Additionally, we compared differences of gene expressions between CORIN highly expressed cairomyocytes and low expressed cardiomyocytes. Moreover, we checked the effects of HDAC2 for cardiac maturaion.
eset.growth_protocol_ch1: Undifferentiated iPSCs were dissociated, and then suspended in StemPro34 medium supplemented with Y-27632 and BMP4 and allowed to form EBs by being placed into 96-well dish. On day 1, media, which included activin A, BMP4 and bFGF, were added into the wells. On day 3, EBs were collected and dissociated, and then suspended in differentiation media supplemented with VEGF and  IWP-3. Approximately 10000-20000 cells were put in each well to again form aggregates for 4 days. On day 7, the media were changed to StemPro 34 media supplemented with VEGF and bFGF. For the maintenance of iPSC-CMs, the culture media were refed every 2-3 days.
eset.extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was prepared using the miRNeasy Purification kit (Qiagen) following the manufacturer's recommendations. RNA was quantified using a NanoDrop-1000 spectrophotometer and quality was monitored with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies).
eset.scan_protocol: Slides were scanned on the G2565CA Microarray Scanner System (Agilent).
eset.data_processing: GeneSpring GX. Signals were normalized to percentile.
eset.contact_department: Center for iPS Cell Research and Application
eset.cell.type.ch1: Undifferentiated human induced pluripotent stem cells
